8 ounces rice vermicelli noodles
1 bunch green onion
1/2 pound snow peas
8 ounces shiitake mushrooms, or mushrooms of choice
1/4 cup coconut oil
1 tablespoon minced garlic
4 cups shredded green cabbage
1 1/4 cups shredded carrots
1 teaspoon coarse sea salt
1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper
1/3 cup coconut aminos, plus more to taste (can sub soy sauce)
1 tablespoon lemon juice, to taste
Add chicken for more protein

HOW TO PREPARE
1.	Prepare rice noodles according to package instructions and set aside.
2.	Meanwhile, dice the onions, separating green and white parts. Cut snow peas into slivers. Slice mushrooms.
3.	In a wok or large pan heat half of the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the garlic, cabbage, whites of onions, and carrots and cook for about 10-12 minutes.
4.	Add the mushrooms and snow peas and cook for an additional 3-5 minutes, or until the veggies are tender.
5.	Add remaining coconut oil and the cooked noodles and stir until the coconut oil is melted and the ingredients are well combined.
6.	Add salt, pepper, coconut aminos, and onion greens. Cook just until heated through and well combined.
7.	Finish with a drizzle of lemon juice and extra soy sauce to taste.
